{
  "stem": "13817.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then from Cuba, he was able to get himself the visa to come into the United States, because he had-- he smuggled jewelry and money into Belgium to an aunt.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And when he got the permission to go to Cuba, he picked it up there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We smuggled money and jewelry into Belgium, but then the, the Germans-- walked into Belgium and sent the aunt away.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I'll never know what happened to it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Everything got lost.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Anyhow, my uncle went to Cuba.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And we-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] To go to Cuba, you had to pull strings with the Cuban government over there, which he was able to do.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So we went on-- we booked passage to Cuba on the ship, which went after the one what Cuba refused to land, where the people were on the boat for months.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And then eventually went back to Holland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And were laying for three weeks in front of Miami, and the American's didn't let them in.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Well, the next ship naturally didn't go anymore.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "We had passage on there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "For Ecuador, we had to-- you had to bribe the consul in Hamburg to get your visa.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "He would give you a visa if you bribed him, which we had done.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "He called to come to Hamburg to pick up the visa.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "My brother took the train at night without-- with taking his star off, because you need special permission to travel, which he didn't have.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And when he came to Hamburg to pick up the visa, they had to-- the night before, they had arrested the consul.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "So this fell through.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Then, my uncle in Colombia, he got the papers ready for us to go to Colombia.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And like South America, there was a revolution every time.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
